## 2026-03-27 - `deleteOrphanVariables` only checks the default "TokenManager" collection — tokens synced to custom collection names (via `collectionMap`) will never be identified as orphans and can't be cleaned up
- Updated `deleteOrphanVariables` to accept a `collectionMap: Record<string, string>` parameter. It now builds a set of all managed collection names (`VARIABLE_COLLECTION_NAME` + all values in `collectionMap`) and iterates over every managed collection when deleting orphans.
- Updated the `delete-orphan-variables` message handler in controller.ts to pass `msg.collectionMap` to the function.
- Updated `PublishPanel.tsx` to include `collectionMap` in the `delete-orphan-variables` message payload (the prop was already available).

